                <pb n="2805" facs="a6eb7f92e15b189aafc2594a2711c4b4.jpg"/>
                <salute>My dearest Mother</salute>

<p>Just a line to say I have<lb/> heard nothing of Charlie<lb/> a Hospital Ship arrived today<lb/> so am asking some one to find<lb/> out if he came on it. I have<lb/> also got the War Office to<lb/> find out where he is but<lb/> will not get an answer<pb/>
           
                <pb n="2806" facs="e9a460819f1f7f2a5add5138e272ebbb.jpg"/>
                till tomorrow but I hope by<lb/> this you will have had good<lb/> news.</p>

<p>I am in the very best of form<lb/> but longing to hear more<lb/> news.</p>

<p>I shall write you a long<lb/> letter to-morrow &amp; tell you<lb/> all the news.</p>
.
<p>I have just received a very nice<lb/> letter &amp; cheque from A. Lessy, which<lb/> I hope to answer tomorrow<lb/> also M. Charles &amp; M. Frank, it<lb/> was so nice &amp; good of them<lb/> all to think of me so far<lb/> away.</p>

<p>Well I hope this will find<pb/>
           
                <pb n="2807" facs="1edec6cc4a3ec28429f4ddb4609b1f2c.jpg"/>
                you very well with good news<lb/> of Charlie. I hope Tommy<lb/> is very well &amp; not gone out yet.</p>

<p>Very best of love to all.</p>

<salute>Yours ever loving</salute>

Marie<lb/>
In great haste.
           
                <pb n="2808" facs="69f9764da362b646b35f53c09fd5bb46.jpg"/>
                On Active Service<lb/>
<hi rend="underline">M.M.</hi>

<address>Mrs Martin<lb/>
Greenbank<lb/>
Monkstown<lb/>
Co Dublin<lb/>
<hi rend="underline">Ireland</hi></address>
           
        </body>
    </text>
     

